
[1]hussar

   HUS'SAR, n. s as z. A mounted soldier of horseman, in German cavalry.
   The hussars are the national cavalry of Hungary and Croatia. Their
   regimentals are a fur cap adorned with a feather, a doublet, a pair of
   breeches to which the stockings are fastened, and a pair of red or
   yellow boots. Their arms are a saber, a carbine and pistols. Hussars
   now form a part of the French and English cavalry.
